3. 養聲
廣東話：個歌手最近聲帶發炎，醫生話佢要靜養，專心養聲先可以返工。
English: The singer's vocal cords are inflamed recently; the doctor said he needs to rest and focus on recovering his voice before he can work again.

4. 票尾
廣東話：你張戲飛嘅票尾仲有冇？要留返做收據先可以退錢。
English: Do you still have the stub of your movie ticket? You need to keep it as a receipt to get a refund.

5. hacker
廣東話：呢個 hacker 好叻，可以幾分鐘內就 hack 入政府嘅電腦系統。
English: This hacker is very skilled; he can hack into the government's computer system within a few minutes.

6. 石斛蘭
廣東話：阿爸好鍾意種石斛蘭，因為佢地係依附喺樹上面生長，好有特色。
English: Dad loves growing Dendrobium orchids because they grow attached to trees, which is very unique.

7. 吊詭
廣東話：呢個情況好吊詭，明明係為咗大家好，結果反而搞到大家更唔開心。
English: This situation is quite paradoxical; it was meant to be for everyone's good, but the result made everyone even unhappier.

8. 吊詭
廣東話：佢嘅論點好吊詭，表面似係有理，但深究落去就發現係荒謬嘅。
English: His argument is quite paradoxical; it seems reasonable on the surface, but upon closer inspection, it turns out to be absurd.

9. 各為其主
廣東話：雖然佢哋以前係好朋友，但而家各為其主，喺商戰入面都唔會留情面。
English: Although they were good friends before, now they each serve their own masters and won't hold back in the business war.

10. 軨蓋
廣東話：部車嘅軨蓋（即係呔軨）壞咗，要快啲去車房修返好先可以行。
English: The car's hood (bonnet) is broken; we need to go to the garage to fix it quickly before we can drive.

11. 打哥夫
廣東話：阿叔退休之後，成日同班老友去球場打哥夫，好享受。
English: After retiring, Uncle often goes to the golf course to play golf with his old friends and enjoys it very much.

12. 免揀
廣東話：呢間店賣嘅蛋糕係免揀嘅，你只可以買佢哋預先包裝好嘅盒裝。
English: The cakes sold in this shop are non-selectable; you can only buy the pre-packaged boxes they have prepared.

13. 擺闊佬
廣東話：佢成日喺人面前擺闊佬，其實佢個戶口入面根本冇幾多錢。
English: He always shows off his wealth in front of people, but actually, he doesn't have much money in his account.

14. 廣播劇
廣東話：我細個好鍾意聽收音機入面嘅廣播劇，特別係嗰啲偵探故事。
English: When I was young, I loved listening to radio dramas on the radio, especially the detective stories.

15. 錄影機
廣東話：以前我屋企有一部錄影機，成日用嚟錄電視節目返嚟睇。
English: My family used to have a video recorder, which we often used to record TV programs to watch later.

16. 吟詩吟唔甩
廣東話：佢偷咗公司嘅錢，證據吟詩吟唔甩，最後只可以認罪。
English: He stole money from the company; the evidence is irrefutable, so he had to confess in the end.

17. 佈道大會
廣東話：下個禮拜日教會會舉辦一個大型佈道大會，歡迎大家參加。
English: The church will hold a large evangelistic meeting next Sunday; everyone is welcome to attend.

18. 寫手
廣東話：佢係一個好有創意嘅寫手，寫出嘅文章好多人鍾意睇。
English: He is a very creative writer, and many people enjoy reading his articles.

19. 寫手
廣東話：呢本書其實係請咗一個寫手代筆寫嘅，作者本人根本冇寫過。
English: This book was actually written by a ghostwriter; the author himself didn't write a single word.

20. 代打
廣東話：我今日冇時間打機，可以請個代打幫我過關嗎？
English: I don't have time to play games today; can I hire a substitute player to help me pass the level?

21. 茶碗
廣東話：日本茶道入面，個茶碗嘅形狀同質感都好重要，係一種藝術。
English: In Japanese tea ceremony, the shape and texture of the tea bowl are very important; it is a form of art.

22. 茶隔
廣東話：沖茶嘅時候，記得用茶隔將茶葉同茶湯分開，咁樣飲落去先唔會塞牙。
English: When brewing tea, remember to use a tea strainer to separate the tea leaves from the tea liquor, so it won't get stuck in your teeth when you drink it.

23. 只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈
廣東話：老闆自己可以遲到早退，但員工遲到就要扣錢，真係只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈。
English: The boss can arrive late and leave early, but if employees are late, they get fined; it's truly "the magistrate is allowed to set fires, but the common people are not allowed to light lamps."

24. 獨唱
廣東話：今晚個演唱會，佢會喺最後一個環節進行獨唱，唱首好感人嘅歌。
English: At tonight's concert, she will perform a solo in the final segment, singing a very touching song.

25. 快人快事
廣東話：佢係個快人快事嘅人，有嘢要幫佢，佢都會即刻幫你搞掂。
English: He is a straightforward person; if you need his help, he will get it done for you immediately.

26. 四腳獸
廣東話：唔好喺公廁入面做四腳獸，好唔衛生又唔文明。
English: Don't engage in "four-legged beast" activities in the public restroom; it's very unhygienic and uncivilized.

27. 無米粥
廣東話：呢個項目仲係煲無米粥嘅階段，大家先唔好期望過高。
English: This project is still in the "cooking rice without rice" stage; everyone shouldn't have expectations that are too high.

28. 義會
廣東話：以前好多低下階層嘅人會參加義會，互相集資幫手解決急需用錢嘅問題。
English: In the past, many people from lower social classes would join mutual aid societies (Yi Hui) to pool funds and help each other solve urgent financial problems.

29. 榜文
廣東話：古代官府有嘢要宣佈，就會喺城門口貼出榜文，俾百姓睇。
English: In ancient times, when the government had something to announce, they would post a notice (Bang Wen) at the city gate for the common people to read.

30. MK 名
廣東話：佢個網名係一個典型嘅 MK 名，前面加咗「堅系」，後面仲有一堆特殊符號。
English: His online username is a typical MK name, starting with "Gin Sai" (堅系) and followed by a bunch of special symbols. [end of text]


